news.title: University of California to invest $4 billion in Blackstone's REIT
news.para: In an unprecedented move, Blackstone exercised its right in November to limit redemptions in the $69 billion BREIT after it received investor requests for redemptions exceeding 5% of the fund's net asset value.

news.title: Court tells civic heads to appear over EWS quarters in Bengaluru's Ejipura
news.para: A division bench headed by Chief Justice Prasanna B Varale observed: "In this situation, we are left with no choice but to direct the commissioner of BDA and chief commissioner of BBMP to be personally present in this court."

news.title: About 43% of homes under PMAY-Urban completed: Assam housing minister
news.para: "We have completed 65,469 units in total and 32,003 houses of them were constructed during the last one year. Around 32,000 more units are at different phases of completion," he added.

news.title: BlackRock defers withdrawals for UK property fund
news.para: Top asset managers, including M&G, Columbia Threadneedle, Schroders and CBRE Investment Management, have imposed restrictions on property fund redemptions since September, after money market turmoil and interest rate rises forced investors to pare exposure to the asset class.

news.title: Rampant illegal construction at Dehradun's Turner road worries locals
news.para: Locals also alleged that various norms are being flouted. Construction is happening on spaces that are supposed to be left vacant around buildings.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation faces criticism for Rajaji Nagar housing scheme delay
news.para: The Smart City Thiruvananthapuram Limited (SCTL) had earlier decided to foreclose the present contract entered with the firm which had bagged the tender in 2020 and to initiate steps for retender.

news.title: Gurugram: Apply for regularisation or face demolition, illegal colonies told
news.para: While 38 applications for regularisation have been received so far by DLSC constituted for the purpose, the deputy commissioner also said that colonies which don’t apply for regularisation by January 18 will have to face demolition.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh HC seeks report on rural housing scheme
news.para: As the finance department and the Andhra Pradesh State Housing Corporation (APSHC) made submissions contrary to each other, the high court directed the finance department to submit action taken report on the proposals sent by APSHC.

news.title: Centre releases Rs 1,671 crore to Uttar Pradesh under PMAY-Rural
news.para: A senior official said that deputy CM Keshav Maurya had written to the Centre suggesting construction of 862767 houses under PMAY-R. So far, about 26 lakh houses have been built in Uttar Pradesh under the scheme.

news.title: Gujarat housing board house owners liable for jantri-linked penalties
news.para: The issue shows that GRUD Act 2022 ignores GHB home owners who want to regularize their illegal extensions . Such property owners seeking regularization of illegal construction will not be entertained.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board notifies need-based changes for dwelling units
news.para: More than 4.5 lakh city residents living in the CHB allotted houses are likely to benefit from the relaxations, which have come into effect after the notification.

news.title: Single-window system for self-redevelopment projects in Maharashtra
news.para: Of the around 1.20 lakh registered cooperative societies and over 80,000 apartments, nearly 60,000 units are over 30 years old and likely to go for redevelopment.

news.title: Panchsheel Greens 2 residents lock society gate over water crisis in Greater Noida
news.para: After facing water disruption from January 1, the residents complained to the Greater Noida Authority, following which a team came to the society to check the pump house. They blamed it on the internal pipeline of the society.

news.title: Gurugram civic body will verify properties again after errors in IDs
news.para: Last year’s survey had concluded that 5.14 lakh properties in areas under MCG’s jurisdiction should be taxed, an increase from the 3.7 lakh on paper till then. Residents alleged that this survey was flawed, with several errors in the property IDs.

news.title: Licensed surveyors and architects to approve G+3 buildings in Kolkata
news.para: KMC officials said architects and LBS will now be able to sanction plans of four-storied buildings (G+3) not exceeding 41ft and with floor area not exceeding 5,382sqft.
